    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Nicotiana Benthamiana sh-Polypeptide-15 Hexapeptide-40 is a fusion peptide of Hexapeptide-40 with a single chain recombinant human peptide produced by  Nicotiana benthamiana  after using either a transient expression system or transgenesis (stable insertion of a copy of a human gene into its DNA). The starting gene is synthesized to be identical to the human gene which codes for Tissue Inhibitor of Metalloproteinases-2 which contains a maximum of 220 amino acids. The fusion peptide contains 200 amino acids and may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
